  "text": "Rice materials. Rice (Oryza sativa) cultivated varieties ZH11 (Zhonghua11), MH63 (Minghui63), DJ (Dongjin), HY (Hwayoung), SSBM (Shi Shou Bai Mao) were used in this study. Callus culture and plant regeneration were performed as described previously [CITATION_1] . Briefly, rice seeds were sterilized and placed on callus induction media for 30 days, then primary callus was transferred to subculture media. After two weeks, callus was used for transformation or transferred to regeneration media. Primary plants regenerated from callus were transferred to rooting media and transferred to field or greenhouse after 1 week. T-DNA mutants, RNAi and over-expression plants were generated by Agrobacterium-mediated transformation using standard callus culture, transformation, selection, and regeneration procedures [CITATION_2] .",
